<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910916-0126</DOCNO><DOCID>910916-0126.</DOCID><HL>   Allied-Signal Air Force Contract</HL><DATE>09/16/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10</SO><CO>   ALD</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><NS>DEFENSE CONTRACTS (DFC)</NS><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><RE>MARYLAND (MD)NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   MORRIS TOWNSHIP, N.J. -- Allied-Signal Inc. said it wasawarded a three-year contract to maintain and modify the U.S.Air Force Space Command's Satellite Control Network.   The contract, valued at $240.6 million with options, wasawarded to the company's Bendix Field Engineering unit inColumbia, Md. The contract calls for maintenance andengineering modification of the network's nine groundstations that control military satellites.</LP><TEXT>   Allied-Signal is an advanced technology company withbusinesses in aerospace, automotive products and engineeredmaterials.</TEXT></DOC>